flow.mentorSays:
Perfect! Here's the optimal solution approach:

```typescript
app.get('/products', (req, res) => {
  const { sort = 'id', order = 'asc' } = req.query;

  const validFields = ['id', 'name', 'price'];
  if (!validFields.includes(sort)) {
    return res.status(400).json({ error: 'Invalid sort field' });
  }

  const sorted = [...products].sort((a, b) => {
    if (order === 'asc') {
      return a[sort] > b[sort] ? 1 : -1;
    } else {
      return a[sort] < b[sort] ? 1 : -1;
    }
  });

  res.json(sorted);
});
```

This solution demonstrates best practices for Nodejs development and shows how to properly implement Array sorting, query params.

